<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="note-vt">note <strong><em>vt</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /nəʊt/    美 /noʊt/  </p>
<p>[正式用语]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>注意；留意：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Please <strong>note</strong> (that) food and fruit are forbidden in the library.
请注意，图书馆内禁止带食品和水果。</p><footer>2013 天津</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Please note how the computer is operated. 
请注意计算机的操作方法。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>特别提到；指出：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>as noted above 
如上所述</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The speaker <strong>noted that</strong> it was very important to set a goal for our life. 
演说者指出为我们的生活设定目标是非常重要的。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="note-down">note down</h3>
<p>1.<strong>记下；记录：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The policeman noted down what I said.
警察记下了我说的话。</p></div>

<h2 id="_3">派生词汇</h2>
<p>noted /nəʊtɪd/ adj   </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Tu Youyou  was <strong>noted for</strong> her bravery for being a scientist during a difficult time for science in China.
屠呦呦因她在中国科学发展困难时期作为一名科学家的勇气而闻名。</p><footer>北师大新必修② – 6</footer></div>

<h2 id="_4">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>Scientists have responded by <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (note) that hungry bears may be congregating(聚集) around human settlements.  （2019 全国）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. noting  </p></div>